# PS
We were stuck with the stub signature during a while. P256 and WebAuthn required distinct stub signatures (using Bundler) which was something unknown to us. Because the real webauthn signature is quite different than the P256 signature, the stub signature must also be different.
* Source: [Pimlico](https://docs.pimlico.io/references/permissionless/reference/pimlico-actions/getPaymasterData#signature)

```ts
const eoatubSignature = "  signature " as Hex;
const webAuthnStubSignature = "" as Hex;
const P256StubSignature = "" as Hex;
const P256NonKeyStubSignature = "" as Hex;
```
